### force-orchestrator (Go daemon + Holocron substrate) ###

# Build output
/force
/force-orchestrator
/force-bash-guard
/bin/

# Legacy agent worktrees that were created inside the repo before the
# .force-worktrees migration. New worktrees are created as siblings of the repo
# at ../.force-worktrees/<repo>/<agent> so they never appear in git status.
# This entry prevents any remaining inside-repo worktrees from being tracked
# as gitlink (mode 160000) entries.
/worktrees/

# Claude Code session state
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# Runtime files
holocron.db*
fleet.db*
fleet.db-shm
fleet.db-wal
fleet.log
fleet.pid
holonet.jsonl
events.jsonl
astromech.log
fleet-task-**

# Test coverage
cover.out
coverage.out
.fix-worktrees/

# Per-deliverable build worktrees (roadmap.md "Worktree discipline").
# Each track of a deliverable runs in `.build-worktrees/D<n>-<track>/` on
# its own `deliverable/<n>/<track>` branch; the directory is disposable
# and never lands on main as tracked content.
.build-worktrees/
.d7-worktrees/
.force-worktrees/

# D6 — `force onboard` produces ONBOARDING.md at the repo root on demand.
# The CLI is operator-triggered, NOT a dog; the rendered file is local-
# only and must never land in git history (anti-cheat directive #2 in
# roadmap §D6). To intentionally commit a sample ONBOARDING.md (e.g. for
# a closure report), copy it to a subdirectory that is NOT named
# /ONBOARDING.md.
/ONBOARDING.md
